Traineeship Title: ERP Functional Practitioner&nbsp;

Traineeship Description: This position reports to the Director of ERP Practice is committed to an employee-orientated, high performance culture that emphasises empowerment, quality, continuous improvement, and on-going development of a superior workplace&nbsp;

Specific Responsibilities: &nbsp;Trainee to be involved in:&nbsp;
1. Attend 10 hours of online ERP Training and Power BI.&nbsp;
2. Provide direct support and assistance during implementation of ERP to clients during the supervision of lead practitioner.&nbsp;

Technical Skills and Competencies Trainee will learn during SGUnited Traineeship Programme:&nbsp;
1. Active participation in strategic planning process, including personal developing goals, objectives and processes &nbsp;
2. How to engage clients and stakeholders professionally &nbsp;
3. Implementation experience with ERP, CRM and Business Intelligence. &nbsp;
4. Industrial knowledge of the functional aspects of financial and supply chain management
5. How to provide business advisory to clients.&nbsp;

Highest Qualification: Bachelor of Science in Computer Science/Engineering/Infocomm/Accountancy

Duration of Traineeship: 12 months&nbsp;

Eligibility Criteria for SGUnitedTraineeships:&nbsp;
a) Singapore Citizen or Permanent Resident;&nbsp;
b) Graduated or graduating in calendar year 2019 or 2020 from ITEs, polytechnics, universities, or other educational institutions (e.g. private universities and overseas institutions); or
Graduated earlier from above institutions and completed National Service in 2019 or 2020.